The core gap appears to be `epistemic->conditional_normative`: the compiler currently has no epistemic target-signal map and no policy-table entry for that pair, so it won’t reliably emit explicit ambiguity for it. I’m now patching registry policy tables plus targeted compiler tests to keep `deontic->deontic` and `frame->temporal` behavior intact while adding the missing pair.
